'''Ngāti Ākarana''' is a [[Māori people|Māori]] cultural club in [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.teara.govt.nz/en/nga-taone-nui-maori-and-the-city/page-5 |title=Ngā tāone nui – Māori and the city – Māori adapt to city life |first=Aroha |last=Harris |date=11 March 2010 |work=Te Ara - the Encyclopedia of New Zealand |accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref> It is a pan-tribal group of Māori who have migrated to Auckland (like [[Ngāti Poneke]] in [[Wellington]] and [[Ngāti Rānana]] in [[London]]). "''Ākarana''" is a [[Māori-language]] approximation of the name ''Auckland''.

